problem:
Calculate $\sqrt{60x} \cdot \sqrt{12x} \cdot \sqrt{63x}$ . Express your answer in simplest radical form in terms of $x$.

Note: When entering a square root with more than one character, you must use parentheses or brackets.  For example, you should enter $\sqrt{14}$ as "sqrt(14)" or "sqrt{14}".
model_solution:
Step 1: $\sqrt{60x} \cdot \sqrt{12x} \cdot \sqrt{63x} = (\sqrt{60x})(\sqrt{12x})(\sqrt{63x})$
Step 2: $(\sqrt{60x})(\sqrt{12x})(\sqrt{63x}) = \sqrt{60x \cdot 12x \cdot 63x}$
Step 3: $\sqrt{60x \cdot 12x \cdot 63x} = \sqrt{60 \cdot 12 \cdot 63 \cdot x \cdot x \cdot x}$
Step 4: $\sqrt{60 \cdot 12 \cdot 63 \cdot x \cdot x \cdot x} = \sqrt{(5 \cdot 2 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 7) \cdot (x^3)}$
Step 5: $\sqrt{(5 \cdot 2 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 7) \cdot (x^3)} = \sqrt{(2^3 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7) \cdot (x^3)} = \sqrt{(2^3 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7 \cdot x^3)} = \sqrt{(2^3 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7 \cdot x^3)} = \sqrt{(2^3 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7 \cdot x^2 \cdot x)} = \sqrt{(2^3 \cdot 3^2 \cdot 5^2 \cdot 7 \cdot x^2)} \cdot \sqrt{x} = (2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot \sqrt{7} \cdot x \sqrt{x})$
Step 6: $2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot \sqrt{7} \cdot x \sqrt{x} = 30x\sqrt{7x}$
Step 7: $30x\sqrt{7x} = 30x\sqrt{7x}$
Step 8: $30x\sqrt{7x} = 30x\sqrt{7x}$
Step 9: $30x\sqrt{7x} = 30x\sqrt{7x}$
Step 10: $30x\sqrt{7x} = 30x\sqrt{7x}$
